radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated, fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 8 mm with a thickened wall, surrounding fat stranding and edema. Mild right-sided hydronephrosis and hydroureter related to the gravid uterus. A single fetus identified in cephalic position. Hemorrhagic corpus luteal cyst on the left ovary. Trace amount of pelvic free fluid. No osseous abnormality.
